1
00:00:44,933 --> 00:00:46,100
Are you out of your mind?

2
00:00:46,167 --> 00:00:48,567
Why did you do that?
Why did you steal that child?

3
00:00:48,633 --> 00:00:50,700
I just took my child.

4
00:00:50,767 --> 00:00:52,333
She's not your daughter.

5
00:00:52,400 --> 00:00:53,500
Your child is dead.

6
00:00:53,567 --> 00:00:56,267
I may have lost my daughter
in a car accident,

7
00:00:56,333 --> 00:01:00,200
but because of this child,
I've been given another chance

8
00:01:00,267 --> 00:01:02,233
to be with my daughter again.

9
00:01:02,300 --> 00:01:06,433
I hope we reunite
in the afterlife.

10
00:01:06,500 --> 00:01:07,533
Are you stupid?

11
00:01:07,633 --> 00:01:09,633
Mookie is allergic to peanuts!

12
00:01:09,700 --> 00:01:12,100
Flor, get the medicine! Hurry!

13
00:01:12,167 --> 00:01:13,333
Why is the tablet here?

14
00:01:13,400 --> 00:01:15,100
What are you watching?

15
00:01:15,167 --> 00:01:16,467
Romantic movies?

16
00:01:16,533 --> 00:01:19,867
Mookie, sweetie, you shouldn't
be watching shows like that.

17
00:01:19,933 --> 00:01:22,433
Because I don't want you
to get your hopes up.

18
00:01:22,500 --> 00:01:23,900
You'll never be normal.

19
00:01:23,967 --> 00:01:27,167
And you'll never find
someone who will love you.

20
00:01:27,233 --> 00:01:29,800
Because he will see
you as a burden.

21
00:01:43,033 --> 00:01:49,267
Hello, Diary.
It's me again, Mookie.

22
00:01:49,333 --> 00:01:53,300
Today is my 17th birthday.

23
00:01:53,367 --> 00:01:57,933
I'm almost an adult,
but why do I feel this way?

24
00:01:58,000 --> 00:02:01,467
Why don't I feel
that I'm already 17?

25
00:02:05,267 --> 00:02:08,367
Ma'am, I'll go out in a bit.
I will have the car tuned up.

26
00:02:08,433 --> 00:02:09,733
Okay. Don't take too long.

27
00:02:09,800 --> 00:02:10,733
Okay, Ma'am.

28
00:02:15,700 --> 00:02:19,767
Because I can't leave the house,

29
00:02:19,833 --> 00:02:23,533
I feel like
I'm missing out a lot.

30
00:02:23,600 --> 00:02:26,267
I don't have friends my age.

31
00:02:26,333 --> 00:02:27,833
I can't go out.

32
00:02:30,300 --> 00:02:31,600
Flor!

33
00:02:31,667 --> 00:02:33,933
- Please close the gate.
- Yes, Ma'am.

34
00:02:37,600 --> 00:02:42,300
I also don't go to a regular
school because I'm homeschooled.

35
00:02:46,067 --> 00:02:47,467
Focus on your work.

36
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:52,867
I always ask myself.

37
00:02:52,933 --> 00:02:59,967
If I'm not sick, can I also do
what the other teenagers do?

38
00:03:00,033 --> 00:03:04,500
Maybe I also don't have to
undergo painful treatments.

39
00:03:06,567 --> 00:03:11,600
Mommy, is that necessary?

40
00:03:11,667 --> 00:03:15,900
You're feeling weak because
you don't have enough potassium.

41
00:03:20,233 --> 00:03:22,233
Mommy, it hurts.

42
00:03:22,333 --> 00:03:24,000
Trust me, sweetie.

43
00:03:24,067 --> 00:03:25,700
Remember?

44
00:03:25,767 --> 00:03:27,433
I'm a doctor.

45
00:03:27,500 --> 00:03:28,733
Don't worry.

46
00:03:28,800 --> 00:03:30,567
This will only take an hour.

47
00:03:42,167 --> 00:03:45,633
Because I'm always at home,

48
00:03:45,700 --> 00:03:48,500
Mommy is my only friend.

49
00:03:48,567 --> 00:03:52,200
But we're not close either.

50
00:03:52,267 --> 00:03:57,100
Because she's only concerned
about my health.

51
00:03:57,200 --> 00:04:00,833
Yes, I know I shouldn't
be saying this.

52
00:04:00,900 --> 00:04:08,300
But I just wonder how it feels
to have a different mom.

53
00:04:08,367 --> 00:04:11,233
Someone who sees not
only my sickness.

54
00:04:38,333 --> 00:04:39,367
Mookie!

55
00:04:39,433 --> 00:04:41,800
Come inside. It's hot in here.

56
00:04:41,867 --> 00:04:44,533
Your mom might see you.

57
00:04:44,600 --> 00:04:45,233
- Flor.
- Go inside.

58
00:04:45,300 --> 00:04:46,333
Come on, come on.

59
00:04:46,400 --> 00:04:48,500
It's so boring
inside the house, Flor.

60
00:04:48,567 --> 00:04:51,833
And Mommy is in the office.

61
00:04:51,900 --> 00:04:56,000
What are you doing here?
You're driving me nuts.

62
00:04:56,067 --> 00:04:58,600
I only want to see them.

63
00:04:58,667 --> 00:05:02,333
What they do is amusing.

64
00:05:02,433 --> 00:05:05,067
And I envy them.

65
00:05:05,133 --> 00:05:06,667
They're so happy.

66
00:05:08,967 --> 00:05:14,067
Okay, you can watch them,
but stay here.

67
00:05:14,133 --> 00:05:16,333
Don't go over there.
You're not allowed to go there.

68
00:05:16,400 --> 00:05:20,000
You might catch a disease
if you get near them.

69
00:05:20,067 --> 00:05:21,200
Stay here.

70
00:05:25,933 --> 00:05:27,400
Hey, bros.

71
00:06:20,533 --> 00:06:24,367
Emma, where are you going?

72
00:06:24,433 --> 00:06:27,533
I'll go to the agency.
I'll find a job.

73
00:06:27,600 --> 00:06:28,633
Wait.

74
00:06:32,467 --> 00:06:34,233
Why?

75
00:06:34,300 --> 00:06:37,567
What happened
to your employer before?

76
00:06:37,633 --> 00:06:40,267
Her family is going to migrate
to another country.

77
00:06:40,333 --> 00:06:43,467
So, I have to look
for a new job.

78
00:06:46,767 --> 00:06:49,700
Can I carry your baby?

79
00:06:49,767 --> 00:06:51,100
Sure, sis.

80
00:06:54,800 --> 00:06:57,033
She's so pretty.

81
00:07:02,567 --> 00:07:03,600
Precious.

82
00:07:06,400 --> 00:07:09,933
Emma, I have a favor to ask you.

83
00:07:10,000 --> 00:07:11,667
What is it?

84
00:07:11,733 --> 00:07:15,567
Can you take care of my child?

85
00:07:15,667 --> 00:07:17,000
What?

86
00:07:17,067 --> 00:07:20,600
- Why?
- I'm leaving for Macau.

87
00:07:20,667 --> 00:07:23,733
I got a job in a casino.

88
00:07:23,800 --> 00:07:27,633
But no one will take care of
Baby Samantha.

89
00:07:27,700 --> 00:07:30,100
I can't leave her to my sister

90
00:07:30,167 --> 00:07:32,500
because she already
has five kids.

91
00:07:32,567 --> 00:07:35,833
I need someone
who can look after her.

92
00:07:35,900 --> 00:07:39,600
I'm willing to pay.

93
00:07:39,667 --> 00:07:40,867
What?

94
00:07:40,933 --> 00:07:43,067
You'll leave Samantha?

95
00:07:43,133 --> 00:07:45,033
She's still so young.

96
00:07:45,100 --> 00:07:48,333
What if something happens
to her while you're away?

97
00:07:48,433 --> 00:07:52,700
Emma, can you please help me?

98
00:07:52,767 --> 00:07:54,467
I'm not sure.

99
00:07:54,533 --> 00:07:57,233
I still have to ask
my husband first.

100
00:07:57,300 --> 00:08:00,033
This is a big responsibility.

101
00:08:00,100 --> 00:08:03,733
But don't you miss
taking care of a baby?

102
00:08:26,667 --> 00:08:30,167
My gosh! There you are, Mookie.

103
00:08:30,233 --> 00:08:32,833
I've been looking for you.
Come on. Let's go inside.

104
00:08:32,900 --> 00:08:33,900
Your mom will be here
any moment.

105
00:08:33,967 --> 00:08:36,033
Can I stay here
a little longer?

106
00:08:36,100 --> 00:08:38,533
Not here. It's so hot in here.

107
00:08:38,600 --> 00:08:41,067
- Let's go.
- Please, Flor.

108
00:08:41,133 --> 00:08:44,833
You know that Mom
confiscated my tablet.

109
00:08:44,900 --> 00:08:47,133
So, please.

110
00:08:47,200 --> 00:08:52,233
I don't want to stay in my room.
There's nothing to do but sleep.

111
00:08:52,300 --> 00:08:54,433
Fine.

112
00:08:54,500 --> 00:08:57,067
Okay. I'll get you an umbrella.
Stay here, okay?

113
00:08:57,167 --> 00:08:59,800
- It's so hot.
- Okay.

114
00:08:59,867 --> 00:09:00,767
Stay there.

115
00:10:31,133 --> 00:10:33,533
Sorry, sorry. Did I hurt you?

116
00:10:33,600 --> 00:10:34,933
Are you hurt?

117
00:10:35,033 --> 00:10:37,933
I'm sorry, I'm sorry.
I didn't notice you.

118
00:10:38,000 --> 00:10:40,400
Are you okay?

119
00:10:40,467 --> 00:10:42,367
Are you hurt?

120
00:10:42,433 --> 00:10:45,733
Are you okay?

121
00:10:45,800 --> 00:10:47,400
I'm Zayn.

122
00:10:47,467 --> 00:10:48,400
What's your name?

123
00:10:55,967 --> 00:10:56,900
Miss! Miss!

124
00:11:09,733 --> 00:11:11,300
Hi!

125
00:11:11,367 --> 00:11:13,800
Olive, here are the
medicines you requested.

126
00:11:13,867 --> 00:11:17,033
Perfect. Thank you.

127
00:11:17,100 --> 00:11:21,000
You know, I really felt bad
for Mookie the other day.

128
00:11:21,067 --> 00:11:24,233
She was really looking
forward to her birthday.

129
00:11:24,300 --> 00:11:27,133
She should be thankful
I even threw her a party.

130
00:11:27,200 --> 00:11:30,067
I only said yes
because who knows?

131
00:11:30,133 --> 00:11:32,833
This could be her last birthday.

132
00:11:32,900 --> 00:11:33,967
Last birthday?

133
00:11:35,900 --> 00:11:37,367
No. I mean,

134
00:11:37,433 --> 00:11:42,433
we can't tell with
Mookie's condition right now.

135
00:11:42,533 --> 00:11:45,033
Olive, I'm sorry.
I don't mean to pry.

136
00:11:45,100 --> 00:11:47,500
But what really
is Mookie's illness?

137
00:11:47,567 --> 00:11:49,600
Last year, it was lupus.

138
00:11:49,667 --> 00:11:53,000
The year before that, leukemia.

139
00:11:53,067 --> 00:11:56,200
Well, Mookie's condition
is very complex.

140
00:11:56,267 --> 00:11:59,333
There are manifestations of
auto-immune diseases like lupus.

141
00:11:59,400 --> 00:12:03,467
But to be honest, at this point,
I still can't determine

142
00:12:03,533 --> 00:12:06,067
specifically what
my daughter's illness is.

143
00:12:06,133 --> 00:12:07,900
It's very hard to tell.

144
00:12:07,967 --> 00:12:11,933
But have you taken her
to the hospital?

145
00:12:12,000 --> 00:12:13,500
What for?

146
00:12:13,567 --> 00:12:14,700
You know, to run some tests

147
00:12:14,800 --> 00:12:16,967
so she can be examined
more thoroughly.

148
00:12:17,033 --> 00:12:21,600
Do you think I can't treat and
take care of my child?

149
00:12:21,667 --> 00:12:23,267
Are you forgetting?

150
00:12:23,333 --> 00:12:24,667
I'm a doctor.

151
00:12:26,333 --> 00:12:29,300
Olive, you didn't finish
med school.

152
00:12:35,367 --> 00:12:39,433
Well, I know enough
to care for my child.

153
00:12:42,633 --> 00:12:44,867
Anyway,

154
00:12:44,933 --> 00:12:45,867
thank you for this.

155
00:12:47,600 --> 00:12:48,967
I have to go.

156
00:12:49,033 --> 00:12:51,267
I need to get this to Mookie.

157
00:12:59,933 --> 00:13:01,600
What?

158
00:13:01,667 --> 00:13:03,700
You'll take care
of someone else's baby?

159
00:13:03,767 --> 00:13:05,900
Come on, Emma.

160
00:13:05,967 --> 00:13:07,467
It's Melissa's child.

161
00:13:07,533 --> 00:13:11,100
She's going to Macau.
No one will care for her baby.

162
00:13:11,167 --> 00:13:14,700
How long will it be?

163
00:13:14,767 --> 00:13:15,900
She still doesn't know

164
00:13:15,967 --> 00:13:19,267
because she has to process
the baby's documents first.

165
00:13:19,333 --> 00:13:22,500
Hey. Think about it carefully.

166
00:13:22,600 --> 00:13:25,133
Caring for a baby isn't easy.

167
00:13:25,200 --> 00:13:27,233
Mom, I did it
with Kayla. Remember?

168
00:13:27,300 --> 00:13:29,500
Emma, that was so long ago.

169
00:13:29,567 --> 00:13:31,233
It's been years.

170
00:13:31,300 --> 00:13:32,767
And one more thing...

171
00:13:32,833 --> 00:13:34,533
you're living a good life.

172
00:13:34,600 --> 00:13:36,367
You don't have
to worry about anything.

173
00:13:36,433 --> 00:13:39,333
You don't need to get up
to tend to a crying baby.

174
00:13:39,400 --> 00:13:41,500
And now, you're going
to raise a child?

175
00:13:41,567 --> 00:13:43,233
Why, Mom?

176
00:13:43,300 --> 00:13:45,833
Don't you miss
having a baby here?

177
00:13:45,900 --> 00:13:47,033
I don't.

178
00:13:50,067 --> 00:13:52,667
Dan, what can you say?

179
00:13:55,267 --> 00:14:00,167
Danilo, talk to your wife.

180
00:14:00,233 --> 00:14:02,300
Many people are waiting for me.

181
00:14:05,733 --> 00:14:10,500
Emma, it's not
that I'm opposing you.

182
00:14:10,567 --> 00:14:13,733
I'm just worried about you.

183
00:14:13,800 --> 00:14:17,533
The baby will stay
with us temporarily.

184
00:14:17,600 --> 00:14:19,400
I know that.

185
00:14:19,467 --> 00:14:23,967
Emma, I'm just scared that
you'll get attached to the kid.

186
00:14:24,033 --> 00:14:27,367
What will happen if Melissa
comes back to get her child?

187
00:14:27,433 --> 00:14:29,767
You might get hurt.

188
00:14:29,867 --> 00:14:33,600
What happened to Baby Kayla
might happen again.

189
00:14:33,667 --> 00:14:37,700
Dan, I'll just take
care of a child.

190
00:14:37,767 --> 00:14:39,133
I'm not going to adopt.

191
00:14:41,433 --> 00:14:43,533
Please?

192
00:14:43,600 --> 00:14:45,933
Okay, I'll think about it.

193
00:14:55,233 --> 00:14:56,900
Slowly.

194
00:14:56,967 --> 00:14:58,867
Ma'am.

195
00:14:58,933 --> 00:15:00,600
Hi, Mommy.

196
00:15:00,667 --> 00:15:02,333
- Hi.
- Hello.

197
00:15:07,633 --> 00:15:10,067
Why?

198
00:15:10,133 --> 00:15:11,600
Give me your hand.

199
00:15:11,667 --> 00:15:15,933
- Mommy, it's okay.
- We always do this, right?

200
00:15:16,000 --> 00:15:18,000
I'll massage you.

201
00:15:32,167 --> 00:15:34,867
What's this?

202
00:15:34,967 --> 00:15:36,033
Where did you get this?

203
00:15:42,967 --> 00:15:44,367
Yes, they's a bit...

204
00:15:44,433 --> 00:15:46,567
right? Yes, that's it.

205
00:15:46,633 --> 00:15:50,767
There. Yes, that's it.

206
00:15:50,833 --> 00:15:52,467
- There.
- Should I order this one?

207
00:15:52,533 --> 00:15:53,700
Yes, that one.

208
00:15:53,767 --> 00:15:55,867
- It looks good.
- Do we get the same color?

209
00:15:55,933 --> 00:15:56,800
Yes.

210
00:15:57,567 --> 00:16:00,700
Hey, girl! Zayn's here.

211
00:16:00,767 --> 00:16:03,467
- Hurry!
- Go!

212
00:16:03,533 --> 00:16:06,433
- Wait.
- Go, girl. Go for it.

213
00:16:14,333 --> 00:16:16,000
Hi, Zayn.

214
00:16:16,067 --> 00:16:18,400
I'm so glad that
you moved here.

215
00:16:18,467 --> 00:16:23,900
At least we can always
hang out together now.

216
00:16:23,967 --> 00:16:26,433
Do you know the girl
who lives there?

217
00:16:26,500 --> 00:16:27,600
Which girl?

218
00:16:27,667 --> 00:16:30,067
The girl who is our age.

219
00:16:30,133 --> 00:16:33,167
Oh my gosh. That weirdo?

220
00:16:33,233 --> 00:16:34,733
Why is she weird?

221
00:16:34,800 --> 00:16:37,000
We don't see her outside.

222
00:16:37,067 --> 00:16:41,767
Ever since they moved here,
she never came out of her house.

223
00:16:41,867 --> 00:16:44,367
I think she has a medical
condition or something.

224
00:16:44,433 --> 00:16:46,600
This is what I'm afraid of.

225
00:16:46,667 --> 00:16:49,567
Is your platelet count dropping?

226
00:16:49,633 --> 00:16:51,867
Has your leukemia relapsed?

227
00:16:51,933 --> 00:16:55,000
Then you're gonna need
another dose of chemo.

228
00:16:55,067 --> 00:16:57,633
- And then what else?
- Mommy! No!

229
00:16:57,700 --> 00:16:59,833
No!

230
00:16:59,900 --> 00:17:02,767
The truth is,

231
00:17:02,833 --> 00:17:06,333
I came out of the house earlier.

232
00:17:07,867 --> 00:17:10,233
I tripped.

233
00:17:10,300 --> 00:17:12,700
You went out?

234
00:17:12,767 --> 00:17:15,133
I did, but...

235
00:17:15,233 --> 00:17:17,900
but, Mommy,
promise I didn't go far.

236
00:17:17,967 --> 00:17:22,467
And this is nothing, Mom.

237
00:17:22,533 --> 00:17:24,467
You went out of the house?

238
00:17:26,367 --> 00:17:30,567
Didn't I tell you
that you can't go out?

239
00:17:30,633 --> 00:17:32,067
It's dangerous out there!

240
00:17:33,233 --> 00:17:35,100
It's just the mom.

241
00:17:35,167 --> 00:17:38,467
And I think she's crazy.

242
00:17:39,767 --> 00:17:42,100
What made you say so?

243
00:17:42,167 --> 00:17:44,433
I heard it from the neighbors.

244
00:17:44,500 --> 00:17:48,600
And I think she locks
up her daughter.

245
00:17:48,700 --> 00:17:50,467
Really?

246
00:17:50,533 --> 00:17:52,800
Poor girl.

247
00:17:52,867 --> 00:17:56,067
Wait. Why are you
interested in them?

248
00:17:56,133 --> 00:17:58,667
They're a family of weirdos.

249
00:17:58,733 --> 00:18:00,367
Don't be like that.

250
00:18:00,433 --> 00:18:02,200
We don't know
what they're going through.

251
00:18:04,433 --> 00:18:07,433
I went out because I saw a bird.

252
00:18:07,500 --> 00:18:09,567
That's all I did, Mommy.

253
00:18:09,633 --> 00:18:10,767
Mommy, sorry.

254
00:18:10,833 --> 00:18:12,933
- Flor.
- Ma'am?

255
00:18:13,000 --> 00:18:14,433
Didn't I tell you

256
00:18:14,500 --> 00:18:19,400
that you'll do nothing but watch
over Mookie when I'm not here?

257
00:18:19,467 --> 00:18:22,800
Ma'am, I left
to get an umbrella.

258
00:18:22,900 --> 00:18:25,533
Mommy! Flor didn't do
anything wrong.

259
00:18:25,600 --> 00:18:27,267
It's my fault.

260
00:18:30,400 --> 00:18:32,300
Then, you should be punished.

261
00:18:34,833 --> 00:18:36,600
What?

262
00:18:36,667 --> 00:18:40,500
Because you disobeyed me,

263
00:18:40,567 --> 00:18:42,633
you'll stay in the dark room.

264
00:18:42,700 --> 00:18:43,700
- Mommy, no!
- Ma'am?

265
00:18:43,767 --> 00:18:45,367
- No, Mommy!
- Ma'am? Ma'am, please don't.

266
00:18:45,433 --> 00:18:46,300
- Ma'am, please don't.
- Mommy, no!

267
00:18:46,367 --> 00:18:48,300
- Ma'am, please don't!
- Come here

268
00:18:48,367 --> 00:18:49,633
- You're so stubborn.
- Mommy, please don't!

269
00:18:49,700 --> 00:18:52,633
Mommy, I don't want
to be in the dark room.

270
00:18:52,700 --> 00:18:55,867
Please, you know
I'm scared of the dark room.

271
00:18:55,967 --> 00:18:57,267
Come here!

272
00:19:00,033 --> 00:19:04,433
When Rapunzel was born,
Mother Gretel took her.

273
00:19:04,500 --> 00:19:06,800
Rapunzel, my foot!

274
00:19:06,867 --> 00:19:09,600
She doesn't understand you!

275
00:19:09,667 --> 00:19:11,533
I'm telling you, Emma.

276
00:19:11,600 --> 00:19:14,333
You'll have a hard
time because of it.

277
00:19:14,400 --> 00:19:18,800
Mom, just because I lost a child

278
00:19:18,867 --> 00:19:21,700
doesn't mean I can
no longer be a mother.

279
00:19:21,767 --> 00:19:24,700
It's a good thing
that Melissa will pay you.

280
00:19:24,767 --> 00:19:27,900
You're going to waste
your time with that child.

281
00:19:28,000 --> 00:19:29,900
You'll earn more
if you get another job.

282
00:19:29,967 --> 00:19:34,600
Mom, I'm not taking care of
Baby Samantha because of money.

283
00:19:37,233 --> 00:19:39,300
Mommy, please! No, Mommy!

284
00:19:39,367 --> 00:19:41,700
- Mommy, please!
- Stay here.

285
00:19:41,767 --> 00:19:42,733
Come here.

286
00:19:45,400 --> 00:19:48,433
- Mommy.
- This is what you get

287
00:19:48,500 --> 00:19:50,967
for disobeying me.

288
00:19:51,033 --> 00:19:54,200
Mommy, please. I'm sorry,
I don't want to be here.

289
00:19:54,267 --> 00:19:56,200
Mommy, please.
I'll do everything.

290
00:19:56,267 --> 00:19:58,767
Promise, Mommy.
Just don't leave me here.

291
00:19:58,833 --> 00:20:00,900
You'll stay here for now.

292
00:20:00,967 --> 00:20:03,900
I want you to think
about what you did.

293
00:20:04,000 --> 00:20:05,100
Mommy, no!

294
00:20:05,167 --> 00:20:09,967
Mommy, please!

295
00:20:10,033 --> 00:20:12,400
Mommy!

296
00:20:12,467 --> 00:20:13,633
No, Mommy! Please!

297
00:20:13,700 --> 00:20:14,967
Mommy!

298
00:20:15,033 --> 00:20:16,167
Mommy!

299
00:20:16,233 --> 00:20:18,067
Mommy!

300
00:20:18,133 --> 00:20:20,633
Mommy!

301
00:20:20,700 --> 00:20:24,333
- Emma, I'm home.
- I'm glad you're back.

302
00:20:24,400 --> 00:20:26,233
Look.

303
00:20:26,300 --> 00:20:27,533
Dan.

304
00:20:27,600 --> 00:20:30,267
I introduce to you, Samantha.

305
00:20:30,333 --> 00:20:32,900
She's the one
I'm telling you about.

306
00:20:32,967 --> 00:20:34,967
Aren't we going to talk
about it first?

307
00:20:35,067 --> 00:20:36,833
That's what I'm telling her!

308
00:20:36,900 --> 00:20:39,033
I don't know.
Your wife is so stubborn.

309
00:20:40,500 --> 00:20:41,700
I feel bad for the baby.

310
00:20:41,767 --> 00:20:43,967
No one's going
to watch over her.

311
00:20:44,033 --> 00:20:45,833
So I took her here for now.

312
00:20:49,133 --> 00:20:49,967
Look.

313
00:20:52,100 --> 00:20:56,167
Emma, can you handle
the responsibility?

314
00:20:56,233 --> 00:20:58,167
We did it with Kayla,
didn't we?

315
00:20:58,233 --> 00:21:00,600
Of course, Kayla's different.

316
00:21:00,667 --> 00:21:02,500
This one isn't our child.

317
00:21:02,567 --> 00:21:03,967
I know.

318
00:21:04,033 --> 00:21:07,833
I will give her back to
Melissa once she returns.

319
00:21:07,900 --> 00:21:10,367
I'm just thinking about you.

320
00:21:10,467 --> 00:21:13,400
You might get hurt.

321
00:21:13,467 --> 00:21:17,567
Dan, you don't have to worry.

322
00:21:17,633 --> 00:21:23,067
You know, since I brought
Baby Samantha home,

323
00:21:23,133 --> 00:21:25,967
I can't help but smile.

324
00:21:26,033 --> 00:21:27,967
Yeah. It shows.

325
00:21:29,467 --> 00:21:31,033
Look at her.

326
00:21:31,100 --> 00:21:32,933
Yeah.

327
00:21:33,000 --> 00:21:38,867
- She's always smiling.
- You're right.

328
00:21:38,933 --> 00:21:40,233
She talks to you.

329
00:23:05,767 --> 00:23:06,733
Mommy.

330
00:23:21,633 --> 00:23:22,567
How are you?

331
00:23:25,500 --> 00:23:27,433
Do you regret going out?

332
00:23:31,200 --> 00:23:32,033
Yes.

333
00:23:34,467 --> 00:23:35,833
Will you do it again?

334
00:23:38,533 --> 00:23:39,733
No, Mommy.

335
00:23:43,167 --> 00:23:44,767
That's my good girl.

336
00:23:46,700 --> 00:23:47,667
Here.

337
00:23:49,367 --> 00:23:52,000
I have something for you.

338
00:23:52,067 --> 00:23:56,400
Of course, I need
to make it up to you.

339
00:23:56,500 --> 00:24:02,200
Because I don't want
you to think that

340
00:24:02,267 --> 00:24:05,633
I'm such a terrible mother.

341
00:24:05,700 --> 00:24:09,333
You know Mookie, sweetie...

342
00:24:09,400 --> 00:24:12,500
I didn't want to do this to you.

343
00:24:12,567 --> 00:24:16,567
But you left me
with no other choice.

344
00:24:16,633 --> 00:24:18,267
I need to teach you a lesson.

345
00:24:18,333 --> 00:24:21,767
So you won't do it again.

346
00:24:21,833 --> 00:24:23,833
Mookie, sweetie.

347
00:24:23,900 --> 00:24:25,833
Mommy loves you.

348
00:24:25,900 --> 00:24:30,267
And I do all this
because I love you.

349
00:24:30,367 --> 00:24:33,533
Because I protect you.

350
00:24:33,600 --> 00:24:37,400
You know the outside world
is very dangerous.

351
00:24:37,467 --> 00:24:39,833
You could die.

352
00:24:39,900 --> 00:24:46,400
And as your mother,
I won't let it happen to you.

353
00:24:46,467 --> 00:24:49,900
That's how much I love you.

354
00:24:49,967 --> 00:24:51,933
Always remember that, okay?

355
00:24:53,600 --> 00:24:55,900
Okay, Mommy.

356
00:24:55,967 --> 00:24:57,433
Good girl.

357
00:25:15,300 --> 00:25:20,200
Other moms do everything
for their children.

358
00:25:20,267 --> 00:25:24,100
Why do you seem like you
don't want me to be happy?

359
00:25:24,167 --> 00:25:31,267
I can't feel your love for me.

360
00:25:31,333 --> 00:25:33,300
You love looking
after that child,

361
00:25:33,367 --> 00:25:34,567
but she's not even
related to you.

362
00:25:34,633 --> 00:25:38,467
Mom, someone doesn't have
to be our blood relative

363
00:25:38,567 --> 00:25:40,133
for us to love them, right?

364
00:25:40,200 --> 00:25:44,667
Haven't you and Danilo talked
about having a baby again?

365
00:25:44,733 --> 00:25:46,633
Poor Mookie.

366
00:25:46,700 --> 00:25:49,233
Just stay out of it.

367
00:25:49,300 --> 00:25:51,867
Ma'am Olive knows
what's best for Mookie.

368
00:25:51,933 --> 00:25:55,067
What are you doing here?
My mom might see you.

369
00:25:55,133 --> 00:25:57,333
I'll just return this.
You dropped it.

370
00:25:57,400 --> 00:25:59,267
I'm already 17.

371
00:25:59,333 --> 00:26:01,833
I'll be an adult soon.

372
00:26:01,900 --> 00:26:08,267
I want to know how it feels
to be in the outside world.

373
00:26:08,333 --> 00:26:09,400
I said no.

374
00:26:12,300 --> 00:26:13,200
You'll stay here.
